According to its photophysical behaviour, a Ca 2+  chemosensor might be included in one of the three following groups: (i) intensometric, (ii) ratiometric or (iii) pseudo-ratiometric chemosensors 174 . The type of sensing influences the relation between the light intensity and the Ca 0 2+  concentration to be measured (i.e. before the calcium ions bind to the sensor in the cell, Fig.  7d–g ). These three types of responses are shortly described below.

